<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
horsey-mod bestiary v1: first shipped extended gene.

`BX_GIANT_BABY` targets render slot 0 with `mode="set"` and pushes the
horse's primary scale parameter to 200.0 when expressed. Slot 0 is the
only empirically-verified visible-effect slot as of 2026-05-15
(see horsey-mod/docs/GENE-CATALOG.md "Confirmed visible-effect slots":
the 2026-05-14 "giant babies" experiment proved a value of 200.0 in
slot 0 renders horses at roughly full screen width).

Authors who want every horse to manifest this effect should call:
  horse.ext.default_alleles.set { ext_gene_idx: 0, maternal: 3, paternal: 3 }
which sets both diploid picks to allele 3 (value 200.0). Lower allele
indices yield smaller scales (0 = no effect, 1 = 50, 2 = 100, 3 = 200).

Deploy: copy this file next to the staged horsey.dll. The mod auto-loads
it at attach via `worker_main`; live re-edits land via the
`genes.ext.reload` HTTP op.
-->
<genes-extended>
  <gene name="BX_GIANT_BABY" ext_idx="0"
        m="100" s="1"
        g0="0" g1="50" g2="100" g3="200">
    <render slot="0" mode="set" />
  </gene>
</genes-extended>
